There is a difference between a joke SCP and a humorous one: what I call the "No, not really," factor. So basically, if an article is written in a way that every sentence seems to say, "no, not really," it's a joke.

And if you want to know the difference: "… must be kept away from dead bodies," vs. "Into the fiery orb with ye."

Since I'm more of the latter, Clef thinks I should stay a mainlist SCP.







